items.name: Elf 1 from Sukebe Elf Tanbouki
items.description:
The first elf from Sukebe Elf Tanbouki.

I don't have a lot of time at the moment so i'm trying to create these between working and the spare time I have. As you can imagine a lot of work goes into the datasets to make the LORA's as best as they can be, sometimes this can take half a day depending on how much stitching, demosaicing + Photoshopping (filling in errors, background characters, etc) there needs to be done.

I will get around to the other 2 elves when I get chance.

The tags "choker, feathers, side ponytail" can be used to further enhance the character. Her nipples tend to go in and out of inverted states, even using inverted_nipples won't help.

After much testing, it seemed like 40 epochs with 3 repeats tended to give a balanced result but might be a little bit overtrained.

EDIT: I have uploaded the 30 epoch version also with generated images. Not sure which people think is better overall? (Personally I feel that 40 epochs is better)

items.name: Genshin Impact All In One | Character Lora 43336
items.description:
Lora trained on 43336 images of all Genshin Impact Characters.

This does not include Male characters, Paimon, Kirara, or NPCs and will not ever.

This took me over 17 hours to make since I only have a 3070ti 8gb.

I release all my models for free, if you feel like supporting me and my work you can support me here and buy me a drink.

Please note that some characters may not come out perfectly due to not individually being able to select the epochs since this is a combined training and not a merge.

This is dim32 so it is only ~40mb instead of having to download all 42 of the loras separately so I hope some people can appreciate it.

items.name: Reality Check
items.description:
Contains Vae. 
It is in .safestensor.
He was trained with old modeling magazines + cartoon covers.
The model allows you to create a realistic style with a laminated touch.

Arr, me hearties! I be recommendin' ye these here features: Eular a, DPM++2s Kerras, DPM++SDE Keras, an' DPM++2M SDE Keras. Eular a be givin' jolly good results even wit' 25 steps, but the more yer put in, the better the booty. Wit' one o' them DPMs, ye'll be seein' amazin' results wit' 30-40 steps, ye scallywags! 512x512 an' 512x768 may not be a blunder, but where it truly shines be at higher resolutions like 768x768 an' 768x1024, arrr! It be workin' its best wit' detailed prompts, but if ye be havin' simpler prompts, it be alright to let the model handle the rest, matey! ⚓️🏴‍☠️

items.name: RPGOwlbear
items.description:
This is a LoRA for creating the dreaded Owlbear for a medieval rpg.
I'm not 100% happy with it, but it's something. I'll keep working on it, but I thought I might as well put a version up that still fits the bill. I did allow the owlbears to have more bear like faces if you want or just make them more traditional owl faces. Weigh them as you like.

items.name: ub1mo Style
items.description:
A clean style with a slight high contrast theme.

How to use
Prompt as normal, things this LoRA is good is androids, colored backgrounds, horns, various skin colors and bigger breasts.

I recommend using "simple background" and/or "yellow background" or any other defined color. You can also add "sphere" and "cables" to positive or negative tags depending on what you want to prompt. There's a lot of images tagged as "extra arms" but they're so varied the tag doesn't work reliably.
For sample prompts see the uploaded images and the zip with training tags. Note that you have to change the LoRA name if you copy my sample prompts, the filename was misspelt as "ub1imo" when they were generated.

There's a lot of images with variable number of limbs and non-human themes which can make image generation a bit chaotic. I recommend generating a large batch at lower resolution first to find a good base image and then using the "Variation seed" option in Automatic1111 to refine it further. You can also use ControlNet poses to help improve results.

MISC
Trained with 120 on NAI at 512 resolution.
All sample images are raw txt2img, cherrypicked, no inpainting or helper embeddings used.
The training was done on a small subset of the artists images, as such the output of this LoRA is not an accurate representation neither in quality or style of the source material. Go support the artist ub1mo if you want the good stuff.

We're happy with the style and output from Linda and have created a persona and chat which you can interact with over on our site. We also wanted to make it so anyone can use Linda on their own computers.

items.name: NIJIBOY
items.description:
Model Introduction: This model simulates the color style generated by niji, with a hazy atmosphere created by the collision of high-saturation colors and grayscale.

Recommended models: allboymix_v20, anyting, etc.

Sampler suggestion: DPM++ 2M Karras, DPM++ 2S Karras, try them yourself.

Lora Weight suggestion: 0.5-0.8

Size suggestion: 512*512 with HD upscale and a redraw factor of 0.55-0.6

CFG Scale: 7-8

First attempt, welcome to leave feedback on the image.

模型简介：该模型为模拟niji生成的色彩风格，高饱和色彩与灰度碰撞的朦胧氛围感。

推荐大模型：allboymix_v20、anyting等

采样方法建议：DPM++ 2M  Karras、DPM++ 2S Karras 自己尝试

权重建议：0.5-0.8

尺寸建议：512*512 开启高清修复，重绘幅度建议0.55-0.6

提示词引导系数建议：7-8

首次尝试欢迎返图留言！
